OL,7,FMore than 440,000 hours of sewage was
OL,8,Freleased along England's coastline in
OL,9,F2023, with thousands of spills taking
OL,10,Fplace close to bathing spots, analysis
OL,11,Fshows.
OL,13,FCampaign group Friends of the Earth
OL,14,Fanalysed Environment Agency data on
OL,15,Fsewage overflow outlets to calculate
OL,16,Fthe number and duration of spills
OL,17,Fdirectly into the sea and estuaries
OL,18,Fand near swimming waters.
