OL,3,C'More than 440,000 hours of sewage
OL,4,Creleased' along England's coastline in
OL,5,C2023
OL,7,FFriends of the Earth identified all
OL,8,Fsewage outflows in coastal or estuary
OL,9,Fwaters, or within 500 metres of the
OL,10,Fsea, to analyse the number and
OL,11,Fduration of spills into the water.
OL,13,FThe campaign group also used the
OL,14,Flocation of coastal bathing waters to
OL,15,Fsummarise sewage spills within the
OL,16,Fvicinity of beaches, and identified
OL,17,Fall swimming spots which had warnings
OL,18,Fnot to swim due to pollution or for
OL,19,Freduced water quality in 2023, to see
OL,20,Fwhere was being most affected.
